Package opennlp.ccg.unify

Interface Summary
Feature An attribute paired with a value, possibly with an index that ties it to another feature.
FeatureStructure A feature structure containing attributes and their associated values.
Indexed An object which can be indexed.
ModFcn Interface for functions which modify Mutable objects.
Mutable Interface for objects which might contain recursive structure and are mutable.
Substitution Specifies how variable are to be replaced to make two objects unify.
Unifiable An interface for classes that may be unified.
Variable A variable that can stand for some class of Unifiable objects.
 

Class Summary
EmptySubstitution A Substitution which does not hold any substitutions.
GFeatStruc A feature structure for use with CCG categories.
GFeatVar A class for variables which can stand for any feature.
GSubstitution Implementation of Substitution interface which ensures that all the categories it contains are updated as new substitutions are made.
GUnifier A unifier for CCG categories.
SelfCondensingSub Implementation of Substitution interface which ensures that all the categories it contains are updated as new substitutions are made.
SimpleSubstitution Simple implementation of Substitution interface.
SimpleType A simple type for feature values in CCG categories.
Unifier A unification utility that abstracts a few basic issues such Variables and not needed to pass a substitution object explictly.
UnifyControl Center of command for the unification process.
 

Exception Summary
UnifyFailure
